or/Li Ya Lee","target":"Author/Li Ya Lee","line":98},{"title":"Author/Li-Ya Lee","target":"Author/Li-Ya Lee","line":99},{"title":"Author/Li Ya Lee","target":"Author/Li Ya Lee","line":100},{"title":"Author/Wan Ping Chen","target":"Author/Wan Ping Chen","line":101},{"title":"Author/Wan-Ping Chen","target":"Author/Wan-Ping Chen","line":102},{"title":"Author/Wan-Ping Chen","target":"Author/Wan-Ping Chen","line":103},{"title":"Author/Chien Chang Shen","target":"Author/Chien Chang Shen","line":104},{"title":"Author/Chien-Chang Shen","target":"Author/Chien-Chang Shen","line":105},{"title":"Author/Chien-Chang Shen","target":"Author/Chien-Chang Shen","line":106},{"title":"Author/Young-Ji Shiao","target":"Author/Young-Ji Shiao","line":107},{"title":"Author/Young Ji Shiao","target":"Author/Young Ji Shiao","line":108},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/tzeng_cyanthin_2018/tzeng_cyanthin_2018.pdf","line":110}],"metadata":{"id":"tzeng_cyanthin_2018","type":"article-journal","title":"The Cyanthin Diterpenoid and Sesterterpene Constituents of Hericium erinaceus Mycelium Ameliorate Alzheimer’s Disease-Related Pathologies in APP/PS1 Transgenic Mice","issued":{"date-parts":[[2018]]},"DOI":"10.3390/ijms19020598","container-title":"International Journal of Molecular Sciences","abstract":"Hericium erinaceus was used in traditional Chinese medicine for physiologically beneficial medicines. Recently, it has become a candidate in causing positive brain health-related activities. We previously reported that Hericium erinaceus mycelium ameliorates Alzheimer’s disease (AD)-related pathologies. To reveal the role of the cyanthin diterpenoid and sesterterpene constituents on this effects, erinacine A and S were isolated and their effects on attenuating AD-related pathology in APPswe/PS1dE9 transgenic mice were investigated. A 30 day short-term administration of erinacine A and S were performed to explore the effect of each erinacine on AD-related pathology including amyloid β production and degradation, plaque formation, plaque growth, glial activation and neurogenesis deterioration. Our results indicated the benefit effects of both erinacine A and S in cerebrum of APPswe/PS1dE9 mice, including: (1) attenuating cerebral plaque loading by inhibiting plaque growth; (2) diminishing the activation of glial cells; (3) raising the level of insulin degrading enzyme; and (4) promoting hippocampal neurogenesis. Moreover, erinacine A reduced the level of insoluble amyloid β and C-terminal fragment of amyloid precursor protein which was not mediated by erinacine S. We further performed a long term administration of erinacine A and found that erinacine A recovered the impairment in the tasks including burrowing, nesting, and Morris water maze. Our data pointed out that although both erinacine A and S reduce AD pathology via reducing amyloid deposition and promoting neurogenesis, erinacine A can also inhibit amyloid β production and is worth to be further developed for AD therapeutic use.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Tzeng","given":"Tsai Teng","literal":""},{"family":"Tzeng","given":"Tsai-Teng","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Chien Chih","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Chien-Chih","literal":""},{"family":"Chien-Chih","given":"Chen","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Chien-Chih","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Chin Chu","literal":""},{"family":"Chin-Chu","given":"Chen","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Chin Chu","literal":""},{"family":"Tsay","given":"Huey Jen","literal":""},{"family":"Tsay","given":"Huey-Jen","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Li Ya","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Li-Ya","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Li Ya","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Wan Ping","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Wan-Ping","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Wan-Ping","literal":""},{"family":"Shen","given":"Chien Chang","literal":""},{"family":"Shen","given":"Chien-Chang","literal":""},{"family":"Shen","given":"Chien-Chang","literal":""},{"family":"Shiao","given":"Young-Ji","literal":""},{"family":"Shiao","given":"Young Ji","literal":""}],"citation-key":"tzeng_cyanthin_2018","year":"2018","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["The Cyanthin Diterpenoid and Sesterterpene Constituents of Hericium erinaceus Mycelium Ameliorate Alzheimer’s Disease-Related Pathologies in APP/PS1 Transgenic Mice"],"author-links":["[[Author/Tsai Teng Tzeng]]","[[Author/Tsai-Teng Tzeng]]","[[Author/Chien Chih Chen]]","[[Author/Chien-Chih Chen]]","[[Author/Chen Chien-Chih]]","[[Author/Chien-Chih Chen]]","[[Author/Chin Chu Chen]]","[[Author/Chen Chin-Chu]]","[[Author/Chin Chu Chen]]","[[Author/Huey Jen Tsay]]","[[Author/Huey-Jen Tsay]]","[[Author/Li Ya Lee]]","[[Author/Li-Ya Lee]]","[[Author/Li Ya Lee]]","[[Author/Wan Ping Chen]]","[[Author/Wan-Ping Chen]]","[[Author/Wan-Ping Chen]]","[[Author/Chien Chang Shen]]","[[Author/Chien-Chang Shen]]","[[Author/Chien-Chang Shen]]","[[Author/Young-Ji Shiao]]","[[Author/Young Ji Shiao]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/tzeng_cyanthin_2018/tzeng_cyanthin_2018.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"1n0nxlw","at":1774951887283}},"smart_blocks:Research/@tzeng_cyanthin_2018.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.00866095,-0.02008888,0.02447237,-0.01876774,-0.01447321,0.01621966,0.0017666,0.05632502,-0.06098471,-0.01823253,0.040383,-0.08330522,0.0517526,0.01519378,-0.00235232,-0.01479103,-0.03047886,-0.00858216,-0.06382511,-0.01677216,-0.02528775,-0.07071755,0.057468,-0.02173704,0.01489496,0.0217479,-0.01115867,0.00383149,-0.06566592,-0.19319655,-0.01127271,-0.02543593,-0.00595118,0.00698949,-0.02833825,-0.00742044,-0.01974193,0.05124177,-0.00177048,-0.02810681,0.05563651,0.07011177,0.00317878,-0.00371925,-0.00462589,-0.05159628,-0.03866337,-0.08748688,0.04254682,-0.00453448,0.0250762,-0.03829686,0.04120244,0.06326205,0.0298